      = *[[Shuva (film)|Shuva]]\n*[[Bhalobaslei Ghor Bandha Jay Na]]\n*[[Khodar Pore Ma]]\n*[[Shikari (2016 film)|Shikari]]\n*[[Nabab]]\n*[[Chalbaaz]]\n*[[Bhaijaan Elo Re]]\n*[[Naqaab (2018 film)|Naqaab]]\n*[[Password (2019 Bangladeshi film)|Password]]\n| style              = *[[Drama film|Drama]]\n*[[Romance film|Romance]]\n*[[Action film|Action]]\n*[[Comedy film|Comedy]]\n| height_m           = \n| height_ft          = \n| weight             = \n| weight_kg          = \n| awards             = [[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]] (3 times) <br /> [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]] (8 times)\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Apu Biswas]]|2008|2017|reason=divorced}}<ref name=\"ds11Apr2017\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Shakib sends divorce letter to Apu |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/online/shakib-khan-apu-biswas-divorce-letter-apu-1500025 |work=The Daily Star |date=4 December 2017}}</ref>\n| children           = 1<ref name=\"ds11Apr2017\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Apu, Shakib end secrecy over marriage |url=http://bdnews24.com/entertainment/2017/04/10/apu-biswas-says-she-has-a-child-with-co-actor-shakib-khan |work=bdnews24.com |date=10 April 2017 |access-date=11 April 2017}}</ref>\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Shakib Khan''' (born March 28, 1979)<ref name=\":happybirthday\">{{cite web|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/post/298191/Happy-birthday-Shakib-Khan|title=Happy birthday, Shakib Khan|last=Culture|first=Desk|date=27 March 2018|website=Daily Sun|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=live|access-date=14 January 2020}}</ref> is a Bangladeshi film actor, producer, singer and media personalities. He started his career with ''[[Ananta Bhalobasha]]'' (1999) directed by Sohanur Rahman Sohan.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|title=\u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac \u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09e8\u09e6 \u09ac\u099b\u09b0 |url=https://mzamin.com/article.php?mzamin=174673 |access-date=15 July 2019 |work=[[Manabzamin]] |date=28 May 2019}}</ref> Subsequently Khan established himself as one of the most successful actors in Bengali cinema.<ref>{{cite news |title=Interview with No. 1 Shakib Khan|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=21980:interview-with-no-1-shakib-khan&catid=175:weekend-independent&Itemid=213 |newspaper=The Independent |location=Dhaka |date=3 December 2010 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130204110953/http://www.theindependentbd.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=21980:interview-with-no-1-shakib-khan&catid=175:weekend-independent&Itemid=213 |archive-date=4 February 2013 |access-date=13 August 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He is popularly known in the media as \"Superstar\", \"King Khan\" and \"Dhallywood King\". Currently he is the highest paid actor in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Saju|first1=Shah Alam|title=I am my own competitor\u2026 Shakib Khan|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/i-am-my-own-competitor-shakib-khan|access-date=14 March 2018|work=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|The Daily Star]]|language=en|date=21 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangla/anandadhara/\u09b8\u09bf\u0995\u09cb\u09af\u09bc\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u09b8/\u099c\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7-\u099c\u09c7\u09a8\u09c7-\u09a8\u09bf\u09a8-\u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac-\u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0-\u099c\u09be\u09a8\u09be-\u0985\u099c\u09be\u09a8\u09be-\u0995\u09bf\u099b\u09c1-\u0985\u09a7\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09af\u09bc-90469|title=\u099c\u09a8\u09cd\u09ae\u09a6\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7 \u099c\u09c7\u09a8\u09c7 \u09a8\u09bf\u09a8 \u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac \u0996\u09be\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u099c\u09be\u09a8\u09be-\u0985\u099c\u09be\u09a8\u09be \u0995\u09bf\u099b\u09c1 \u0985\u09a7\u09cd\u09af\u09be\u09af\u09bc|last=|first=|date=28 May 2018|website=The Daily Star|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nKhan has received various awards, including three [[Bangladesh National Film Award for Best Actor|National Film Awards for Best Actor]], for ''[[Bhalobaslei Ghor Bandha Jay Na]]'' (2010),<ref>{{cite news |title=National Film Award 2010 announced |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=227182 |newspaper=The Daily Star |agency=BSS |date=21 March 2012 |access-date=12 December 2014}}</ref> ''[[Khodar Pore Ma]]'' (2012),<ref name=\"dt12May2014\">{{cite news |last=Chaity |first=Afrose Jahan |date=12 May 2014 |title=National Film Award celebrates Bangladeshi film history |url=http://archive.dhakatribune.com/entertainment/2014/may/12/national-film-award-celebrates-bangladeshi-film-history |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |access-date=16 January 2017}}</ref> and ''[[Aro Bhalobashbo Tomay]]'' (2015)<ref name=\"bdnews24\">{{cite web |url=http://www.gbangla24.com/full_news.php?NID=17373 |title=Shakib take top acting honours in National Film Awards 2015 |work=bdnews24 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007130005/http://www.gbangla24.com/full_news.php?NID=17373 |archive-date=7 October 2015 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and Eight [[Meril Prothom Alo Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Meril Prothom Alo Awards Gala Night |url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/news/65879/Meril-Prothom-Alo-Awards-Gala-Night |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=9 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"prothom-alo.com\">{{cite news |title=Shakib Khan Dedicate his eight award to his son |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/entertainment/article/1153141/%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%89%E0%A7%8E%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%97-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AC |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=21 April 2017 |language=bn}}</ref>\nShakib is also a producer. His first produced movie was ''[[Hero: The Superstar]]'' under his own banner SK films.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jalil, Shakib head to head for Box Office dominance |url=http://archive.newagebd.net/34988/jalil-shakib-head-to-head-for-box-office-dominance/ |newspaper=New Age |location=Dhaka |date=27 July 2014 |access-date=16 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newagebd.net/article/48039/im-hopeful-of-global-release-of-my-films-shakib-khan |title=I'm hopeful of global release of my films: Shakib Khan |website=[[New Age (Bangladesh)|New Age]] {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken Daily English Newpaper in Bangladesh |access-date=25 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nShakib Khan was born in [[Muksudpur]], [[Gopalganj District, Bangladesh|Gopalganj]], [[Bangladesh]]. His father Abdur Rab was a government officer and his mother Nurjahan is a housewife. His father's original home district was in Gopalganj. His father's profession required the family to relocate frequently from one city to another during his school years. [[Secondary School Certificate]] (SSC)<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u09a8\u09be\u09ae\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09b0 \u0993\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09a8 \u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac \u0996\u09be\u09a8 |trans-title=Number One Shakib Khan |url=http://www.dailyjanakantha.com/news_view.php?nc=20&dd=2011-03-17&ni=52648 |language=bn |newspaper=Janakantha |date=17 March 2011 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130215215200/http://www.dailyjanakantha.com/news_view.php?nc=20&dd=2011-03-17&ni=52648 |archive-date=15 February 2013 |access-date=3 January 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n=== 1999 \u2013 2005 ===\nShakib Khan was first contracted sign in the film ''[[Sobai to Sukhi Hote Chay]]'' ({{trans|Everyone wants to be happy}}), he was first to stand in front of the camera with this film, which was directed by Aftab Khan Tulu, another newcomer Karisma Sheikh played opposite him. Although Khan's debut film was ''[[Ananta Bhalobasha]]'' ({{trans|Everlasting love}}) directed by [[Sohanur Rahman Sohan]], which was released on May 28, 1999. [[Erin Zaman]], the younger sister of actress [[Moushumi]], played opposite him in the film, and it has become notable as the debut film of both. Although the film was not very successful but Khan as a hero caught the attention of everyone. In the second year of his acting career, he appeared in the film ''[[Golam]]'' (2000) opposite then the top actress [[Shabnur]] directed by [[Ispahani Arif Jahan|Ispahani-Arif Jahan]] duo. On this year, he starred opposite [[Purnima (Bangladeshi actress)|Purnima]] in the film ''[[Ajker Dapot]]'' directed by AJ Rana, ''[[Dujon Dujonar]]'' opposite [[Popy]] directed by [[Abu Saeed Khan]], and ''[[Bishe Bhora Nagin]]'' opposite [[Moon moon]] directed by [[Delwar Jahan Jhantu]].\n\nIn 2001 several films released by him including ''[[Shikari (2001 film)|Shikari]]'', ''[[Shopner Bashor]]'', ''Mayer Jehad'', ''Rangga Mastan'', ''Hingshar Poton'' and ''Bondhu Jokhon Shatru''. ''[[Shopner Bashor]]'' directed by [[F I Manik]], along with [[Riaz]] and [[Shabanur]] his performance also praised by the critics and audience in the film. In 2002 a number of films released by him including ''Ful Nebo Naa Ostro Nebo'' and ''[[Strir Morjada]]'' ditected by [[F I Manik]], ''[[O Priya Tumi Kothay]]'' directed by [[Shahadat Hossain Liton]], ''Nachnewali'' by [[Zillur Rahman (director)|Zillur Rahman]] and ''Bishwa Batpar'' by Badal Khandaker. In the film ''Strir Morjada'' he first time ever appear opposite [[Moushumi]].\n\nIn 2003, he starred in ''[[Sahoshi Manush Chai]]'', ''[[Praner Manush]]'', ''[[Kkhmotar Dapot]]'' and ''[[Sobar Upore Prem]]''. The film ''[[Sahoshi Manush Chai]]'' directed by Mohammed Hannan, which was highly acclaimed by the critics and audience and won the [[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]] in two categories.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u099c\u09be\u09a4\u09c0\u09af\u09bc \u099a\u09b2\u099a\u09cd\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 \u09aa\u09c1\u09b0\u09b8\u09cd\u0995\u09be\u09b0 \u0995\u09bf \u0986\u099f\u0995\u09c7 \u09af\u09be\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7?|url=http://archive.prothom-alo.com/detail/news/11823|newspaper=[[Prothom Alo]]|author=Kamruzzaman |date=2009-10-13|access-date=2 March 2016}}</ref> In 2004, he starred in ''[[Noyon Bhora Jol]]'', ''[[Ajker Somaj]]'', ''[[Bostir Rani Suria]]'' and ''[[Rukhe Darao]]''. In 2005, he starred in ''[[City Terror]]'' directed by M A Rahim, he first time performed with [[Manna (actor)|Manna]] in the film. He also starred with [[Riaz]] and [[Purnima (Bangladeshi actress)|Purnima]] in the film of ''[[Badha]]'' directed by Shahin\u2013Sumon.\n\nKhan's films include: ''[[Amar Swapno Tumi]]'' (2005), ''Chachu'' (2006), ''[[Koti Takar Kabin]]'' (2006), ''Dadima'' (2006), ''Biye Bari'' (2006), ''[[Doctor Bari]]'' (2007), ''[[Pitar Ason]]'' (2007), ''Ek Takar Bou'', ''[[Mone Prane Acho Tumi]]'' (2008), ''[[Tumi Swapno Tumi Shadhona]]'' (2008), ''[[Amar Praner Priya]]'' (2009), ''[[Mone Boro Kosto]]'' (2009), ''[[Shaheb Name Golam]]'' (2009), ''Jaan Amar Jaan'' (2009), ''Bhalobashar Lal Golap'' (2009), ''[[Bolbo Kotha Bashor Ghore]]'' (2009), ''Preme Porechi'' (2010), ''[[Poran Jaye Jolia Re (2010 film)|Poran Jaye Jolia Re]]'', ''[[Nissash Amar Tumi]]'' (2010), ''Hai Prem Hai Bhalobasa'' (2010), ''[[Matir Thikana]]'' (2011), ''[[Tiger Number One]]'' (2011), ''[[Boss Number One]]'' (2011) ''Tor Karone Beche Achi'' (2011), ''Priya Amar Jaan'' (2011), ''[[King Khan (film)|King Khan]]'' (2011), ''[[Mayer Morjada]]'' (2006), ''[[Amar Praner Swami]]'' (2007), ''[[Priya Amar Priya]]'' (2008), ''[[Bhalobaslei Ghor Bandha Jay Na]]'' (2010), ''[[Number One Shakib Khan]]'' (2010), ''[[Khodar Pore Ma]]'' (2012), ''[[Don Number One]]'' (2012), ''[[My Name Is Khan (2013 film)|My Name Is Khan]]'' (2013), ''[[Bhalobasha Aaj Kal]]'' (2013), ''[[Purno Doirgho Prem Kahini]]'' (2013), ''Faand: The Trap'' (2014), ''[[Hero: The Superstar]]'' (2014), ''[[Purno Doirgho Prem Kahini 2]]'' (2016), ''[[Samraat: The King Is Here]]'' (2016), ''[[Mental (2016 film)|Mental]]'' (2016), ''[[Shikari (2016 film)|Shikari]]''<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |title=New Indo-Bangla joint production starts |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/new-indo-bangla-joint-production-starts-1196158 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=19 March 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news |title=Shikari: Shakib's first Indo-Bangla venture |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2016/mar/16/shikari-shakibs-first-indo-bangla-venture |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |date=16 March 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160608215946/http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2016/mar/16/shikari-shakibs-first-indo-bangla-venture |archivedate=8 June 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite news |title=Shakib looks like Salman: Adnan |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2016/may/10/shakib-looks-salman-adnan |newspaper=Dhaka Tribune |date=10 May 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160609223950/http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2016/may/10/shakib-looks-salman-adnan |archivedate=9 June 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite news |title=Check out Shakib\u2019s menacing \"Shikari\" look |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/arts-entertainment/check-out-shakibs-menacing-%E2%80%9Cshikari%E2%80%9D-look-1235188 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=6 June 2016 |accessdate=16 June 2016}}</ref> (2016), ''[[Bossgiri]]'' (2016), [[Chalbaaz]] (2018), and others.<ref name=\"ds28Apr2011\">{{cite news |last=Shazu |first=Shah Alam |date=28 April 2011 |title=Shakib Khan Numero Uno |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=183430 |newspaper=The Daily Star |access-date=2 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2011 to 2015 he was the president of the Film Artist Association and is engaged in various cultural activities.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shakib Khan to promote 'Power' drink |url=http://www.banglanews24.com/English/detailsnews.php?nssl=3eef284e80280be9aff8a80800dae3f3&nttl=2013010361249&toppos=6 |newspaper=banglanews24.com |date=3 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012190141/http://www.banglanews24.com/English/detailsnews.php?nssl=3eef284e80280be9aff8a80800dae3f3&nttl=2013010361249&toppos=6 |archive-date=12 October 2013 |accessdate=3 January 2013}}</ref> He is also the brand ambassador of Pran Power Energy drink<ref>{{cite news |script-title=bn:\u09ac\u09bf\u099c\u09cd\u099e\u09be\u09aa\u09a8\u099a\u09bf\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7 \u09b6\u09be\u0995\u09bf\u09ac \u0996\u09be\u09a8 |trans-title=Advertisement Shakib Khan |url=http://www.prothom-alo.com/detail/date/2013-01-03/news/318266 |language=bn |newspaper=Prothom Alo |date=2 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130105021643/http://www.prothom-alo.com/detail/date/2013-01-03/news/318266 |archive-date=5 January 2013 |accessdate=2 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Shakib Khan become brand ambassador of 'Pran Power Energy drink' |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=263728 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=3 January 2013 |accessdate=3 January 2013}}</ref> and Asian Duplex Town.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asiantownbd.com/latest.php?pd=35 |title=Film star Sakib Khan now in Asian Town |website=Asian Town Development Ltd. |date=24 February 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701070620/http://asiantownbd.com/latest.php?pd=35 |archive-date=1 July 2013 |accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nKhan married actress [[Apu Biswas]] in a private wedding ceremony at Khan's Gulshan house in Dhaka on 18 April 2008, but kept it secret until 2017. Their son (Abraham Khan Joy) was born on 27 September 2016.<ref name=\"ds11Apr2017\">{{cite news |title=I married Shakib Khan in 2008 and they separated in 2018 |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/shakib-khan-married-me-1389424 |work=The Daily Star |date=11 April 2017 |access-date=11 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/showtime/2017/04/10/apu-marriage-baby-shakib/ |title=Apu reveals nine years of marriage, baby with Shakib |accessdate=11 April 2017 |work=Dhaka Tribune |date=10 April 2017}}</ref>\nSince 2011, Shakib Khan has been the president of the Film Artist Association till 18 May 2017.<ref name=\"priyo20110520\">{{cite news |title=Bangladesh film artist association election |url=http://news.priyo.com/video/2011/05/20/bangladesh-film-artist-associa-26583.html |language=bn |work=Priyo News |date=20 May 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220140051/http://news.priyo.com/video/2011/05/20/bangladesh-film-artist-associa-26583.html |archive-date=20 December 2013 |accessdate=12 December 2014}}</ref> He has also done some philanthropic work, such as supporting the [[2013 Savar building collapse|Rana Plaza]] cause. On 10 February 2014 he launched his own production house,  ''SK Films''.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n==Filmography==\n{{main|Shakib Khan filmography}}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n'''[[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]]'''\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-  style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Year !! Award !!  Category !! Film !! Result\n|-\n| 2010 || [[National Film Awards (Bangladesh)|National Film Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Bhalobaslei Ghor Bandha Jay Na]]''<ref name=\"ds28Mar2012\">{{cite news |last=Shazu |first=Shah Alam |date=28 March 2012 |title=Winning streak |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=227983 |newspaper=The Daily Star |access-date=12 December 2014}}</ref>|| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2012 || National Film Award || Best Actor || ''[[Khodar Pore Ma]]''<ref name=\"dt12May2014\" /> ||{{won}}\n|-\n| 2015 || National Film Award || Best Actor || ''[[Aro Bhalobashbo Tomay]]''<ref name=\"bdnews24\"/> ||{{won}}\n|}\n\n'''[[Meril Prothom Alo A